Legend for LISA Cluster Map Not Significant High-High Low-Low Low-High High-Low

📝 In this study, significance was determined through 99,999 permutations. Results were mapped only when the p-value for that location was less than 0.05. Local Indicators of Spatial Association (LISA) were used to identify patterns of spatial clustering for each time period across the study areas. Hotspots of TB incidence during 2014-2023 were mostly detected in Nai Mueang, Phra Lab, and Ban Pet Sub-districts, while coldspots were only detected in Tha Phra Sub-district in 2019. Low-high outliers were detected in Phra Lab in 2014 and Ban Pet in 2021.
